member that EQ come from D&D rules, eventhough not straight from the book and after a while EQ kinda has its own rules. But the point is, you keep playing as remote ROLE PLAYING character.. if you dont like to ROLE PLAY.. play doom or quake they have a lot of ppl playing too.. including the ones that afk and let their character getting blast for 20mins because still counting their paycheck and taxes.<br><br>Its not pathetic when you solo for couple of hours to help someone or even get some for yourself.. but it IS pathetic when you think everyone should know your life and having playing taking out the fun..<br><br>The truth is.. i have job that require 8hours everyday, i do have friends, i do cook for me sometimes (but sometimes call in and take out while playing EQ) hehe. If you think your life worth noticing, just think about how many ppl that have same job like you and keep playing the game? I LOVE grouping and i encourage everyone i meet in game or outside the game to get group and get to know other ppl ALL the time. This is MULTIPLAYER game.. Interaction is one of the fun that this game has.<br><br>You think i dont have any friend? BAH.. as soon as i got online, at least 2 ppl say hi and ask me to get group with them. They know i play fast and furious, but when i went chat.. i sit around kelethin or felwhite and CHAT.. i do not pull and CHAT.. <br><br>My record playing EQ so far is 26hours non-stop.. its sad but if you look it from other side of the fact, i ENJOY to play EQ so much that i forgot how many hours it been passing by. I do have life outside EQ, but again i can always cancel dentist appointment or lunch with some friend that gonna sit around coffe bar and smoke. So everything i believe in balance and harmony.. no need to look down on other ppl when they LOVE to play.<br><br>Btw.. how old are you? Im only 23 and im feeling fine so far.. my girlfriend play EQ and we meet in game and chatting how beautifull the waterfall nearby lake omen. When she play.. (monky) she pull like madman.. and i love that. Now.. who dont have the life? you? or me? (try remember i have full time job as i mentioned above.. but when you love something, it always cure for your broken back) :)<br> <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
